This paper deals with secure compilation, which is a topic closely related to computer security. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses compilers and programming languages, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper involves formal methods and proofs, which could place it in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also deals with modular design, which is a topic relevant to software engineering, and could place it in cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper involves the use of memory isolation mechanisms, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control).
